			<h1><span class="less"><a href="index.html">SLE 2011</a> paper:</span><br><i>Reconstructing Complex Metamodel Evolution</i></h1>
			<h2><a href="../profile/SanderDVermolen.html">Sander D. Vermolen</a>, <a href="../profile/GuidoWachsmuth.html">Guido Wachsmuth</a>, <a href="../profile/EelcoVisser.html">Eelco Visser</a></h2>
<ul><li>DOI: <a href="https://doi.org/10.1007/978-3-642-28830-2_11">10.1007/978-3-642-28830-2_11</a></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t2b.html"><span class="tagM">T2B: Evolution</span></a><ul><li> The paper addresses metamodel evolution, a central maintenance problem in model-driven engineering.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t2a.html"><span class="tagL">T2A: Lifecycle</span></a><ul><li> It focuses on recovery/reconstruction of evolution histories from existing artifacts.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t4b.html"><span class="tagL">T4B: Horizontal Transformation</span></a><ul><li> Reconstructing evolution implies deriving migration mappings/transformations between metamodel versions.
</li></ul></li></ul>
